1
00:00:01,068 --> 00:00:02,903
narrator: Previously on
"jojo’s bizarre adventure"...

2
00:00:04,438 --> 00:00:05,873
( Polnareff gasps )

3
00:00:06,874 --> 00:00:08,309
Young polnareff: What the?!

4
00:00:08,342 --> 00:00:10,277
Why am I a kid?!

5
00:00:10,310 --> 00:00:12,279
Young silver chariot: Pami!

6
00:00:12,312 --> 00:00:14,381
Woman: Little boy,
are you all right there?

7
00:00:14,414 --> 00:00:17,884
I’ll clean those wounds up
and put some medicine on you.

8
00:00:17,918 --> 00:00:19,887
( Polnareff groans )

9
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:21,855
( Alessi cackles )

10
00:00:21,889 --> 00:00:23,157
( Polnareff wails )

11
00:00:23,190 --> 00:00:25,526
That’s impossible!

12
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:26,960
Chariot, help!

13
00:00:30,297 --> 00:00:32,132
Alessi: Yes! Yes!

14
00:00:34,134 --> 00:00:35,335
- ( Polnareff groans )
- ( Silver chariot screams )

15
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:42,442
( Polnareff screams )

16
00:00:42,476 --> 00:00:46,380
I’m not strong enough
to beat him like this.

17
00:00:46,413 --> 00:00:48,015
- ( Gasps )
- Silver chariot: Pami!

18
00:00:48,048 --> 00:00:49,983
Polnareff: I don’t see
that nice lady anywhere.

19
00:00:50,017 --> 00:00:53,087
where’d she go?
She couldn’t have just vanished.

20
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:54,822
She was sitting
right behind me.

21
00:00:54,855 --> 00:00:58,092
I didn’t even hear a scream.
What’d he do to her?

22
00:00:58,125 --> 00:01:00,094
( Alessi laughs )

23
00:01:00,127 --> 00:01:02,296
polnareff:
Where could she have gone?!

24
00:01:02,329 --> 00:01:04,064
Alessi: Oh, polnareff...

25
00:01:04,097 --> 00:01:06,099
( Polnareff gasping )

26
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:09,269
Alessi: As I recall, you said
the shampoo stings your eyes,

27
00:01:09,303 --> 00:01:12,506
and since it looks like
you’ve got some in there...

28
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:19,079
Allow me to help you
wash it out!

29
00:01:19,112 --> 00:01:21,314
Now this won’t take long.

30
00:01:21,348 --> 00:01:23,250
( Polnareff gurgling )

31
00:01:27,487 --> 00:01:29,489
♪

32
00:01:31,525 --> 00:01:33,527
( Singing in Japanese )

33
00:01:52,513 --> 00:01:54,882
( Polnareff gurgling )

34
00:01:54,915 --> 00:01:56,417
C’est mauvais!

35
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:59,520
Having pint-sized arms is
gonna wind up getting me killed!

36
00:01:59,553 --> 00:02:02,923
If only these stupid arms of
mine were just a little longer,

37
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:05,826
i’d be able to poke his eyes out
and make a run for it.

38
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,530
alessi:
So, even in the face of death,

39
00:02:10,564 --> 00:02:11,965
you thought to pull the plug!

40
00:02:11,999 --> 00:02:14,001
However...

41
00:02:15,502 --> 00:02:18,005
- ( Laughs )
- ( Polnareff gurgling )

42
00:02:18,038 --> 00:02:21,408
( Alessi laughs ) With your hair
clogging the water’s only exit,

43
00:02:21,441 --> 00:02:24,411
it’ll take even longer
for the tub to completely drain.

44
00:02:24,444 --> 00:02:27,414
I’d say you have five,
maybe 10 minutes left.

45
00:02:30,951 --> 00:02:33,887
you may as well
throw in the towel now.

46
00:02:33,921 --> 00:02:36,424
You’re going down
for a permanent nap!

47
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:39,492
good night!
Horrid dreams, you little brat!

48
00:02:39,526 --> 00:02:40,494
( Silver chariot gasping )

49
00:02:40,527 --> 00:02:43,063
Alessi: Now die!

50
00:02:43,096 --> 00:02:45,165
( Laughs ) How does it feel

51
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:47,935
knowing that you’re
utterly helpless, polnareff?

52
00:02:47,968 --> 00:02:50,003
( Laughs )

53
00:02:53,574 --> 00:02:54,542
( Bubbles popping )

54
00:02:54,575 --> 00:02:55,576
( Polnareff sighs )

55
00:02:55,609 --> 00:02:58,145
♪

56
00:02:59,813 --> 00:03:00,947
Alessi: Hmm?

57
00:03:00,981 --> 00:03:03,784
W-what the hell is that thing?

58
00:03:03,817 --> 00:03:05,485
( Gasps ) It can’t be!

59
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:07,454
But from the shape and color,
it looks like--

60
00:03:07,487 --> 00:03:09,122
there’s no way!

61
00:03:09,156 --> 00:03:10,824
No one in their right mind

62
00:03:10,858 --> 00:03:13,761
would think of doing something
so downright disgusting!

63
00:03:17,164 --> 00:03:18,932
( Screams )

64
00:03:18,966 --> 00:03:21,936
It’s undeniable!
The smell proves it!

65
00:03:21,969 --> 00:03:23,370
Ugh! How foul!

66
00:03:23,403 --> 00:03:25,472
You took a shit in the bathtub!

67
00:03:25,506 --> 00:03:27,742
- ( Wailing )
- ( Polnareff gasping )

68
00:03:30,143 --> 00:03:32,379
guess i’m
not so helpless after all,

69
00:03:32,412 --> 00:03:34,314
you creepy, four-eyed asshole!

70
00:03:34,348 --> 00:03:37,251
Alessi: How dare you
do something like that?!

71
00:03:37,284 --> 00:03:41,555
Dear god! Isn’t there a shred
of human decency in your body?!

72
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:43,390
What kind of hero
would ever stoop

73
00:03:43,423 --> 00:03:45,292
to doing something
so disturbing?!

74
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:48,061
You are a bad boy, very bad!

75
00:03:48,095 --> 00:03:51,098
Polnareff: Shut up, and tell me
what you did to that nice lady!

76
00:03:51,131 --> 00:03:53,133
I wanna know right now!

77
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:54,135
Where are you?

78
00:03:54,168 --> 00:03:56,103
Where’d you go?!

79
00:03:56,136 --> 00:03:58,538
Lady, answer me!

80
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:00,040
Hey, lady!

81
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:01,274
Alessi: Hmm.

82
00:04:01,308 --> 00:04:02,876
( Laughs )

83
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:05,312
Come on. You that stupid?

84
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:07,347
What do you think I did?

85
00:04:07,381 --> 00:04:08,916
Whoa, there!

86
00:04:08,949 --> 00:04:10,317
It’d be wise for both of us

87
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:12,853
to watch where we step,
polnareff.

88
00:04:12,886 --> 00:04:14,888
One wrong move,
and your lady friend

89
00:04:14,922 --> 00:04:16,490
is likely to be
squashed underfoot.

90
00:04:16,523 --> 00:04:18,091
Huh?

91
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:19,159
( Gasps )

92
00:04:20,827 --> 00:04:22,829
( Weak crying )

93
00:04:29,236 --> 00:04:31,772
Polnareff: He--he wouldn’t.

94
00:04:31,805 --> 00:04:34,908
there’s no way.
This can’t be happening.

95
00:04:34,942 --> 00:04:37,912
- ( Gasps )
- ( Fetus mewling )

96
00:04:37,945 --> 00:04:40,314
Polnareff: No, it can’t be.

97
00:04:40,347 --> 00:04:42,115
Alessi: Anyone who’s
unfortunate enough

98
00:04:42,149 --> 00:04:44,385
to come into contact
with my stand

99
00:04:44,418 --> 00:04:46,487
experiences time in reverse.

100
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,956
Luckily for you,
you saw me coming

101
00:04:48,989 --> 00:04:51,825
and jumped away from my shadow
at the last second,

102
00:04:51,859 --> 00:04:54,462
buying yourself a few more years
than your friend down there,

103
00:04:54,495 --> 00:04:56,197
but she had the misfortune

104
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:58,466
of touching my shadow
for several seconds,

105
00:04:58,499 --> 00:05:01,135
which is the reason
she became a fetus!

106
00:05:01,168 --> 00:05:03,370
( Laughs )

107
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:05,372
She’s alive for the time being,

108
00:05:05,405 --> 00:05:07,507
but, if i’m
being honest with you,

109
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:11,745
she won’t last long outside
the safety of her mother’s womb.

110
00:05:11,778 --> 00:05:12,879
That’s what she gets!

111
00:05:12,913 --> 00:05:14,782
She should have
never tried to help

112
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:17,051
a pathetic piece
of trash like you!

113
00:05:17,084 --> 00:05:18,485
What a moron.

114
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:20,454
( Polnareff yells )

115
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:23,957
You are the worst kind
of person on this planet!

116
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:26,193
( Alessi laughs )

117
00:05:26,226 --> 00:05:27,828
( Polnareff grunts )

118
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:33,000
Crap! You gotta be
kidding me. I just...

119
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:34,968
( Gasping )

120
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:37,004
( Alessi laughs ) Oops!

121
00:05:37,037 --> 00:05:39,006
Looks like you touched it again,

122
00:05:39,039 --> 00:05:41,542
which means you’re
going to get even younger.

123
00:05:41,575 --> 00:05:43,877
this time,
you’ll probably regress

124
00:05:43,911 --> 00:05:46,380
to a diminutive four-year-old
version of yourself.

125
00:05:46,413 --> 00:05:48,015
Polnareff: Not again!

126
00:05:50,884 --> 00:05:53,053
- ( Alessi chuckling )
- Polnareff: This isn’t good.

127
00:05:53,086 --> 00:05:55,355
I have to hurry
and beat this guy,

128
00:05:55,389 --> 00:05:57,358
or the nice lady will--

129
00:05:57,391 --> 00:05:58,893
at this rate,

130
00:05:58,926 --> 00:06:02,096
she only has a matter of minutes
before she dies!

131
00:06:02,129 --> 00:06:04,832
I’ve gotta find a way
to defeat this alessi freak,

132
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:07,201
and i’ve gotta do it fast!

133
00:06:07,234 --> 00:06:09,403
( Alessi chuckles )

134
00:06:09,436 --> 00:06:13,006
Polnareff: She took me in
and fixed up all my wounds.

135
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,775
She was so caring.

136
00:06:14,808 --> 00:06:16,209
I have to hurry!

137
00:06:16,243 --> 00:06:18,412
There’s absolutely
no time to waste.

138
00:06:18,445 --> 00:06:20,147
Alessi: Come here, little boy!

139
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:22,816
Come here! Come here!
( Cackles )

140
00:06:22,850 --> 00:06:24,518
Get over here, will you?!

141
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:26,987
where exactly
do you think you’re going?

142
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,990
You’re not gonna get far
cradling a dying fetus!

143
00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:31,491
Here’s a fun idea.

144
00:06:31,525 --> 00:06:35,029
Let’s turn you into a fetus!

145
00:06:35,062 --> 00:06:37,031
Polnareff: Damn it.
Not this again!

146
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:39,500
His dumb shadow
keeps touching me!

147
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:42,436
( Gasping )

148
00:06:42,469 --> 00:06:45,238
oh, no!
I’m getting even smaller!

149
00:06:45,272 --> 00:06:46,240
Alessi: Yahoo!

150
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:47,808
Oh, boy!

151
00:06:47,841 --> 00:06:50,143
There’s no way in hell
i’m gonna lose now!

152
00:06:50,177 --> 00:06:51,945
Judging from your appearance,
polnareff,

153
00:06:51,979 --> 00:06:53,948
you’re what,
three years old now?

154
00:06:53,981 --> 00:06:55,516
Before you know it,

155
00:06:55,549 --> 00:06:58,352
your intellect will be that
of a three-year-old’s as well.

156
00:06:58,385 --> 00:06:59,987
( Laughs )

157
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,154
( Growls )

158
00:07:01,188 --> 00:07:03,824
( Polnareff whimpering )

159
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:06,226
( Pounding )

160
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:08,362
( Alessi laughs )

161
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:14,301
Locking the door won’t
do you any good, little one.

162
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,044
Polnareff: Made it.

163
00:07:24,077 --> 00:07:26,780
Huh? Damn it. The stupid bars
are too close together!

164
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:29,716
Even a kid can’t slip through.

165
00:07:30,984 --> 00:07:33,487
But I have to find
a way to get out of here,

166
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:36,189
or that freak show’s
gonna kill us both! Crap!

167
00:07:36,223 --> 00:07:38,358
( Silver chariot whimpers )

168
00:07:38,392 --> 00:07:40,861
Polnareff: I-I can’t cut them.

169
00:07:40,894 --> 00:07:43,263
( Alessi laughs )

170
00:07:43,297 --> 00:07:45,533
this is
just too good to be true.

171
00:07:45,566 --> 00:07:48,502
I see that your chariot
has also become a toddler.

172
00:07:48,535 --> 00:07:51,271
The bars are too tough
for its baby rapier.

173
00:07:51,305 --> 00:07:53,274
I bet it’s gotten slower, too.

174
00:07:53,307 --> 00:07:54,975
( Polnareff whimpering )

175
00:07:55,008 --> 00:07:57,978
Alessi: Ready or not,
here I come.

176
00:08:09,523 --> 00:08:11,725
( Babbling )

177
00:08:13,927 --> 00:08:17,731
Oh, polnareff,
here comes alessi!

178
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:19,199
Huh?

179
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:25,772
H-he’s gone.

180
00:08:25,806 --> 00:08:27,941
Huh? Where did he go?

181
00:08:27,975 --> 00:08:30,511
That brat. He just vanished.

182
00:08:30,544 --> 00:08:32,513
Or maybe the little spunk monkey

183
00:08:32,546 --> 00:08:35,883
found a way to slither
through the bars in the window.

184
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,785
( Growls )

185
00:08:37,818 --> 00:08:39,787
( Gasps )

186
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:42,423
Clever, polnareff. Very clever.

187
00:08:42,456 --> 00:08:45,225
You’re trying to pull
a fast one, aren’t you?

188
00:08:45,259 --> 00:08:47,495
You think if you
trick me into believing

189
00:08:47,528 --> 00:08:49,830
you slipped through the window,
it’ll distract me.

190
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:53,133
You must be hiding somewhere,
waiting to get the drop on me.

191
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:56,504
( Laughs ) Not bad, runt.

192
00:08:56,537 --> 00:08:59,807
Quite cunning indeed,
for a miserable little shit!

193
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:03,711
Polnareff, come out,
come out, wherever you are.

194
00:09:03,744 --> 00:09:06,880
( Laughs )
You’re so puny now,

195
00:09:06,914 --> 00:09:09,817
you could easily be hiding
in that drawer over there.

196
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:13,854
Yeah, he’s probably hiding
in the bucket or the drawer,

197
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:18,024
or maybe he’s actually hiding
in that Teddy bear by the wall.

198
00:09:18,058 --> 00:09:19,927
( Snickers )

199
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,462
Oh, where could he be?

200
00:09:21,495 --> 00:09:23,197
I’ve got a one-in-three chance.

201
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:24,932
And, if at all possible,

202
00:09:24,965 --> 00:09:27,234
i’d like to get him
with one swing.

203
00:09:27,267 --> 00:09:30,237
i’ll crack open his
infantile skull with this ax!

204
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:32,272
( Polnareff whimpering )

205
00:09:35,275 --> 00:09:37,210
Alessi: I’ve decided
you’re tucking away

206
00:09:37,244 --> 00:09:40,247
in that tattered,
old Teddy bear!

207
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,449
But my second guess is...

208
00:09:42,482 --> 00:09:44,117
This grandfather clock,

209
00:09:44,151 --> 00:09:46,420
the perfect hiding spot
for a coward!

210
00:09:49,256 --> 00:09:50,224
( Groans )

211
00:09:50,257 --> 00:09:53,360
I guess I was wrong.

212
00:09:53,393 --> 00:09:55,896
Then maybe he’s...

213
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:58,765
Hiding in this rusty bucket!

214
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:00,134
But i--

215
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:02,369
( groans )

216
00:10:02,402 --> 00:10:05,171
So you are in the bear!

217
00:10:05,205 --> 00:10:06,406
( Gasping )

218
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:09,209
Then how about the drawer?!

219
00:10:10,210 --> 00:10:11,545
Where is he?! Where is he?!

220
00:10:11,578 --> 00:10:13,513
Where is he?! Where is he?!
Where is he?!

221
00:10:13,547 --> 00:10:14,548
Where is he?!

222
00:10:14,581 --> 00:10:17,984
H-he’s gone! But how?

223
00:10:18,018 --> 00:10:21,021
There’s no way he could
have gotten out of here!

224
00:10:21,054 --> 00:10:24,090
The walls, floor, and ceiling
are all stone.

225
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:25,826
Even if they were
one centimeter thick,

226
00:10:25,859 --> 00:10:27,427
chariot couldn’t break through.

227
00:10:27,461 --> 00:10:29,797
and those bars
are too narrow for him.

228
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:31,799
I saw it with my own eyes.

229
00:10:31,832 --> 00:10:33,834
This is insane. Where is he?

230
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,435
Where did he go?

231
00:10:35,469 --> 00:10:38,806
- ( Polnareff chuckles )
- alessi: Huh?

232
00:10:38,839 --> 00:10:41,975
polnareff: So you were
outsmarted by a toddler, huh...

233
00:10:42,009 --> 00:10:45,312
- Alessi: What the...
- Polnareff: Old man alessi.

234
00:10:45,345 --> 00:10:46,379
( Alessi gasps )

235
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:50,183
( Polnareff laughing )

236
00:10:54,521 --> 00:10:56,223
Alessi: What’s going on here?

237
00:10:56,256 --> 00:10:58,825
The goldfish just disappeared.

238
00:11:01,061 --> 00:11:03,130
Huh? ( Gasps )

239
00:11:05,199 --> 00:11:07,201
( Shrieking )

240
00:11:11,572 --> 00:11:12,873
( Alessi shrieking )

241
00:11:12,906 --> 00:11:15,575
polnareff: I was hiding
in the fish tank the whole time

242
00:11:15,609 --> 00:11:17,845
and used this mirror
for camouflage.

243
00:11:17,878 --> 00:11:19,980
A kid could have
figured out my plan,

244
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:21,781
and you totally fell for it!

245
00:11:21,815 --> 00:11:24,685
I was worried that something
so simple wasn’t gonna work,

246
00:11:24,718 --> 00:11:28,355
but lucky for me, you’re just
as stupid as you are creepy!

247
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:32,993
It doesn’t matter if chariot’s
stuck in his two-year-old form.

248
00:11:33,026 --> 00:11:35,362
He can still skewer
your face, dumb-ass!

249
00:11:35,395 --> 00:11:37,297
( Laughs )

250
00:11:37,331 --> 00:11:39,567
( Alessi groans )

251
00:11:40,734 --> 00:11:42,970
( Shrieks )

252
00:11:43,003 --> 00:11:45,772
Bad boy! Bad boy!

253
00:11:45,806 --> 00:11:47,541
polnareff:
Hey, get your ass back here!

254
00:11:47,574 --> 00:11:49,476
- Silver chariot: Pami!
- Polnareff: Hey, wait!

255
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:51,879
Until you break your stand’s
spell, i’m gonna keep attacking!

256
00:11:51,912 --> 00:11:53,714
( Fetus whimpers )

257
00:11:53,747 --> 00:11:55,882
Alessi: Bad boy! Bad boy!

258
00:11:55,916 --> 00:11:58,585
You’re such a bad boy!

259
00:11:58,619 --> 00:11:59,787
Polnareff: Of all the--

260
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:01,889
that jerk
jumped out the window!

261
00:12:05,759 --> 00:12:07,961
Alessi: Bad boy.
What a horrible boy.

262
00:12:07,995 --> 00:12:08,963
Eh?

263
00:12:08,996 --> 00:12:11,699
♪

264
00:12:11,732 --> 00:12:13,367
( Shrieks )

265
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,868
( Thinking )
Jotaro.

266
00:12:14,902 --> 00:12:18,572
Crap. If he’s here,
then i’m done for.

267
00:12:18,605 --> 00:12:20,474
How’d he find us?

268
00:12:20,507 --> 00:12:22,509
Jotaro: Hmm.

269
00:12:22,543 --> 00:12:24,678
( Alessi gasping )

270
00:12:24,711 --> 00:12:26,713
♪

271
00:12:29,316 --> 00:12:32,920
jotaro: Someone falling
from a window, covered in blood.

272
00:12:32,953 --> 00:12:34,922
You don’t see that every day.

273
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:36,824
Alessi: Stay calm. Stay calm.

274
00:12:36,857 --> 00:12:40,694
At times like this, the winner
is the one who stays calm.

275
00:12:40,727 --> 00:12:42,629
Just think about it, alessi.

276
00:12:42,663 --> 00:12:45,666
Jotaro must be looking for
the adult version of polnareff.

277
00:12:45,699 --> 00:12:47,768
He has no clue who I am.

278
00:12:47,801 --> 00:12:49,469
I’ll do what I always do,

279
00:12:49,503 --> 00:12:50,971
play dumb until the last minute,

280
00:12:51,004 --> 00:12:53,940
then attack him
when he least expects it.

281
00:12:53,974 --> 00:12:56,643
( Groaning )

282
00:12:56,677 --> 00:12:58,412
O-oh, no!

283
00:12:58,445 --> 00:13:02,916
My boss is going to be so very
angry with me when he finds out!

284
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:04,852
There I was cleaning the window,

285
00:13:04,885 --> 00:13:06,854
and I suddenly slipped
and fell through!

286
00:13:06,887 --> 00:13:08,655
What am I going to do?

287
00:13:08,689 --> 00:13:11,825
What am I going to do?
I am in so much trou--

288
00:13:11,859 --> 00:13:14,362
polnareff: Hold it right there,
you frizzy-haired freak show!

289
00:13:14,394 --> 00:13:15,862
- ( Jotaro gasps )
- ( Polnareff gasps )

290
00:13:15,896 --> 00:13:18,265
Hey, mister! Uh...

291
00:13:18,298 --> 00:13:19,800
What was his name again?

292
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:21,268
Come on. What was it?

293
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:22,803
( Groans )

294
00:13:22,836 --> 00:13:23,804
Alessi: Now’s my chance.

295
00:13:23,837 --> 00:13:25,372
I was waiting for polnareff

296
00:13:25,405 --> 00:13:27,374
to poke his annoying
little head out.

297
00:13:27,407 --> 00:13:29,576
Gotcha now, jotaro!

298
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:31,812
( Polnareff gasps ) Mister,
watch out for his shadow!

299
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:35,982
Alessi: I did it!
I really did it.

300
00:13:36,016 --> 00:13:38,685
I managed to touch
jotaro’s shadow!

301
00:13:38,719 --> 00:13:39,720
Polnareff: Mister, no!

302
00:13:39,753 --> 00:13:42,256
( Alessi laughs )

303
00:13:42,289 --> 00:13:44,258
So, jotaro, how does it feel

304
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:46,593
to be placed
under the spell of my stand?

305
00:13:46,627 --> 00:13:49,463
( Jotaro gasping )

306
00:13:49,496 --> 00:13:51,531
This feeling...

307
00:13:51,565 --> 00:13:53,434
This is...

308
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:54,635
Polnareff: This is bad.

309
00:13:54,668 --> 00:13:57,471
He’s turning into a kid
just like I did!

310
00:13:57,504 --> 00:14:00,707
alessi: Oh, jotaro,
I heard through the grapevine

311
00:14:00,741 --> 00:14:02,443
that you’ve
only recently developed

312
00:14:02,476 --> 00:14:03,744
your stand, star platinum,

313
00:14:03,777 --> 00:14:06,313
and that means
you didn’t have the ability

314
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:08,915
to use your stand
when you were a kid,

315
00:14:08,949 --> 00:14:11,752
so now you’re nothing
but ordinary!

316
00:14:11,785 --> 00:14:15,422
( Laughing )

317
00:14:15,455 --> 00:14:16,656
( Polnareff gasps ) Oh, no!

318
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:18,592
He’s been turned
into a little boy!

319
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:23,663
It looks like he can’t be
any older than a seven-year-old!

320
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:25,299
Alessi: Guess i’m the winner.

321
00:14:25,332 --> 00:14:26,633
Hope you’re watching,
master dio,

322
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:28,335
’cause i’m about to kill jotaro.

323
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:30,337
You’d better give me
a good reward

324
00:14:30,370 --> 00:14:31,705
for everything
i’ve gone through.

325
00:14:31,738 --> 00:14:35,008
Now, jotaro, it’s time to die!

326
00:14:35,042 --> 00:14:37,311
( Groans )

327
00:14:37,344 --> 00:14:38,612
Polnareff: Whoa, what a hit.

328
00:14:38,645 --> 00:14:40,747
he decked him
using only his little-kid fist!

329
00:14:40,781 --> 00:14:43,851
♪

330
00:14:43,884 --> 00:14:45,519
Jotaro: Oh, good grief.

331
00:14:45,552 --> 00:14:47,988
Don’t underestimate me
just ’cause i’m a kid.

332
00:14:48,021 --> 00:14:50,023
( Alessi whimpering )

333
00:14:53,894 --> 00:14:54,795
Jotaro: Ora! Ora!

334
00:14:54,828 --> 00:14:56,797
( Yelling )

335
00:14:56,830 --> 00:14:58,598
Ora!

336
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:04,371
alessi: What?!
You’re seriously telling me

337
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:07,374
that jotaro could kick ass
even as a little kid?!

338
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:08,842
Polnareff: I knew he was tough,

339
00:15:08,876 --> 00:15:11,379
but he was that strong
as a kid? Badass!

340
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:13,413
( Alessi grunting )

341
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:19,886
- ( Groans )
- ( Birds tweeting )

342
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:20,921
( Crash )

343
00:15:22,356 --> 00:15:24,725
( Muttering )

344
00:15:24,758 --> 00:15:26,627
Huh?

345
00:15:26,660 --> 00:15:29,329
( Groans )

346
00:15:29,363 --> 00:15:30,497
( Chuckles )

347
00:15:30,531 --> 00:15:32,633
- ( Footsteps )
- ( Gasping )

348
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:35,569
( Polnareff chuckles )

349
00:15:35,602 --> 00:15:38,538
You got off easy, friend,
but I can fix that.

350
00:15:38,572 --> 00:15:40,374
( Alessi whimpering )

351
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:45,745
( Silver chariot and
star platinum chuckle )

352
00:15:45,779 --> 00:15:46,747
( Alessi shrieks )

353
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:48,782
( Star platinum yelling )

354
00:15:51,818 --> 00:15:53,586
Alessi: Attaboy!

355
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:55,555
( Narrator reading )

356
00:16:04,998 --> 00:16:07,200
♪

357
00:16:12,739 --> 00:16:14,608
( Woman sighs )

358
00:16:14,641 --> 00:16:16,643
( Gasping )

359
00:16:18,445 --> 00:16:20,647
Was all of that a dream?

360
00:16:20,681 --> 00:16:21,916
( Gasps )

361
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:29,556
this earring
belongs to that boy,

362
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:31,725
so it really did happen.

363
00:16:31,758 --> 00:16:33,593
I don’t know why,

364
00:16:33,627 --> 00:16:36,630
but for some reason,
I couldn’t move my body.

365
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:37,731
That’s right.

366
00:16:37,764 --> 00:16:39,899
I may not have
been able to move,

367
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:41,568
but I remember everything.

368
00:16:41,602 --> 00:16:45,372
That sweet little boy devoted
himself to protecting me

369
00:16:45,405 --> 00:16:48,642
and risked his life
by fighting against a grown man.

370
00:16:48,675 --> 00:16:51,778
He had such a brave
and heroic heart.

371
00:16:51,812 --> 00:16:53,847
Oh, where did that boy go?

372
00:16:53,881 --> 00:16:58,519
where--where did
my little knight run off to?

373
00:16:58,552 --> 00:17:01,321
Where did you go?
Where are you?!

374
00:17:03,891 --> 00:17:06,861
Polnareff: I’ve never met
such an amazing woman before,

375
00:17:06,894 --> 00:17:09,296
so kind, so genuine.

376
00:17:09,329 --> 00:17:11,464
That was a close one,

377
00:17:11,498 --> 00:17:14,301
but thankfully
i’m back to my normal self.

378
00:17:14,334 --> 00:17:16,469
I wonder if she’s okay.

379
00:17:16,503 --> 00:17:17,504
- ( Footsteps )
- hmm?

380
00:17:17,538 --> 00:17:18,906
( Gasps )

381
00:17:18,939 --> 00:17:20,507
( Sighs )

382
00:17:22,509 --> 00:17:24,811
Woman: Uh, uh,
I hate to bother you,

383
00:17:24,845 --> 00:17:27,681
but you didn’t happen to see
a sweet, little boy

384
00:17:27,714 --> 00:17:29,883
leave my house in something
of a hurry, did you?

385
00:17:29,917 --> 00:17:31,986
He has silver hair.

386
00:17:32,019 --> 00:17:34,889
come to think of it,
it looks exactly like yours.

387
00:17:34,922 --> 00:17:36,924
( Polnareff gasping )

388
00:17:43,564 --> 00:17:44,865
Woman: Pardon me for asking,

389
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:46,900
but have the two of us
met before?

390
00:17:50,537 --> 00:17:52,572
- ( Gasps )
- Polnareff: No,

391
00:17:52,606 --> 00:17:54,608
I didn’t see
a kid come through.

392
00:17:54,641 --> 00:17:56,643
Sorry I couldn’t help you.

393
00:17:56,677 --> 00:17:57,878
Let’s go, jotaro.

394
00:17:57,911 --> 00:18:00,247
( Jotaro sighs )

395
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:01,848
Polnareff: Come on. Hurry up.

396
00:18:01,882 --> 00:18:04,752
Woman: Uh, wa--please wait!

397
00:18:04,785 --> 00:18:05,853
Could you be--

398
00:18:05,886 --> 00:18:08,222
that earring you’re wearing...

399
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:12,226
Polnareff: The two of us
have never met before.

400
00:18:12,259 --> 00:18:14,261
It’s not possible.

401
00:18:14,294 --> 00:18:18,431
My friend and I are travelers,
so if you’ll excuse us,

402
00:18:18,465 --> 00:18:20,968
there’s another town
we need to get to.

403
00:18:21,001 --> 00:18:23,270
We’ll be going now.

404
00:18:26,707 --> 00:18:29,677
Woman: It was only a dream.

405
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:30,711
Too bad.

406
00:18:36,917 --> 00:18:38,218
( Polnareff groans )

407
00:18:38,252 --> 00:18:40,721
Not a single word
from you, jotaro.

408
00:18:40,754 --> 00:18:43,790
I don’t wanna hear it.
( Groans )

409
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,528
( Jotaro chuckles )

410
00:18:48,562 --> 00:18:51,732
joseph: Oh!
Jotaro and polnareff!

411
00:18:51,765 --> 00:18:54,668
where in the world
have you two slackers been?!

412
00:18:54,701 --> 00:18:57,537
polnareff: Ah!
Mr. Joestar and avdol!

413
00:18:57,571 --> 00:18:59,773
Joseph: How many times
have I told the two of you

414
00:18:59,806 --> 00:19:01,775
not to go wandering off
on your own?

415
00:19:01,808 --> 00:19:03,376
polnareff: Oh,
you’re in a position to talk!

416
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:05,579
You’re the ones
who just disappeared!

417
00:19:05,612 --> 00:19:07,280
- Joseph: Eh?
- Avdol: Now, now.

418
00:19:07,314 --> 00:19:09,850
why don’t we focus
on getting something to eat?

419
00:19:09,883 --> 00:19:11,385
Polnareff: Huh? Hey, iggy!

420
00:19:11,418 --> 00:19:13,954
where the hell
have you been all day long?!

421
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:15,188
( Iggy sighs )

422
00:19:15,189 --> 00:19:17,158
♪

423
00:19:17,191 --> 00:19:18,192
( Overlapping chatter )

424
00:19:18,225 --> 00:19:20,294
Waiter: Can I take that for you?

425
00:19:20,327 --> 00:19:22,129
( Joseph gulping )

426
00:19:22,162 --> 00:19:25,098
Yeah, thanks a million.

427
00:19:25,132 --> 00:19:27,334
Eh, it’s about time.

428
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:29,469
We’re finally getting
a bit of relief.

429
00:19:29,503 --> 00:19:31,372
Avdol: It was quite
the late breakfast,

430
00:19:31,405 --> 00:19:33,140
but I suppose
it couldn’t be helped.

431
00:19:33,173 --> 00:19:34,474
Avdol: Yeah.

432
00:19:34,508 --> 00:19:36,610
Joseph: Since we’ve
almost made it to Cairo,

433
00:19:36,643 --> 00:19:40,013
I think it’s time we figured out
where dio is hiding out.

434
00:19:40,047 --> 00:19:41,415
♪

435
00:19:41,448 --> 00:19:43,250
Polnareff: Oh, we’re doin’ this?

436
00:19:43,283 --> 00:19:44,785
Jotaro: Will it appear?

437
00:19:44,818 --> 00:19:47,421
joseph: I’m not sure,
but given that we’re so close,

438
00:19:47,454 --> 00:19:49,222
the results
should be more precise.

439
00:19:49,256 --> 00:19:51,325
All right, here we go!

440
00:19:51,358 --> 00:19:55,729
( Yells )

441
00:19:58,365 --> 00:20:01,401
Waiter: Excuse me, sir.
Is there a problem over here?

442
00:20:01,435 --> 00:20:03,637
Avdol: Everything’s fine.
Mind your own business.

443
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:05,539
Waiter: Uh, yes, sir.

444
00:20:05,572 --> 00:20:08,542
Joseph: Hmm.

445
00:20:08,575 --> 00:20:12,145
Jotaro: Old man, tell us.
what is it?

446
00:20:12,179 --> 00:20:14,348
Joseph: Just a little longer.

447
00:20:14,381 --> 00:20:18,552
I see something.
It’s getting clearer.

448
00:20:18,585 --> 00:20:19,686
Huh?

449
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,288
Take a good look!

450
00:20:21,321 --> 00:20:23,490
♪

451
00:20:23,524 --> 00:20:26,360
There you have it, gentlemen,
our final destination!

452
00:20:26,393 --> 00:20:27,594
( All grunt )

453
00:20:35,602 --> 00:20:37,604
♪

